<HEADLINE>Gate House commands good price for offices</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>STEWART MCINTOSH</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>FEATURE</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>SCOTLANDS BUSINESS,PROPERTY</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>979484815</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A GLASGOW office deal worth #2.8m demonstrates the underlying
investment demand for good-quality city-centre properties which are let
to prestigious clients, according to agents Lambert Smith Hampton. Gate
House, an office property at 201/203 West George Street, has just been
sold for the above sum by the agents on behalf of Albany Life Assurance
in an off-market deal.
Tenants in the multi-let property include: Allied Dunbar, Clerical
Medical &amp; General, and the Skipton Building Society. The investment was
bought by a discretionary fund client of Baring Houston &amp; Saunders,
introduced by Gee &amp; Co.
Stephen Inglis of Lambert Smith Hampton said: ''We have achieved a
good price for this property, illustrating further the strength of the
investment market for well let buildings in prime situations.
''This deal, together with the forward funding of office developments
at 183 St Vincent Street and 227 St West George Street on a speculative
basis, demonstrates the confidence that institutional investors now have
in the prime Glasgow office market.''
</TEXT>
