<TEXT>
* THREE second-half goals in six minutes from Stirling Albion pushed
Meadowbank Thistle deeper into the Division 2 relegation myre in
Edinburgh last night before just 165 supporters.
Albion manager Kevin Drinkell fielded new-signing Gary Paterrson from
Dunfermline. And he had a happy debut, giving his new club the lead in
74 minutes. His shot was blocked and went spiralling into the air where
Paterrson was first to react, getting his head to the ball and sending
it into the net from six yards.
Joe McLeod was the supplier for Stirling's second goal, scored by
Craig Taggart, with Ian McInnes completing the scoring with a well-hit
shot from an acute angle.
</TEXT>
