<HEADLINE>Kiwis collapse</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>26</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484853</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SOUTH Africa yesterday completed a win against New Zealand by 93 runs
on the final day of the one-off Test in Auckland.
On a remarkable day's cricket, South Africa set New Zealand 275 in two
sessions to win and bowled them out for 181. Seamer Fanie de Villiers
spearheaded the collapse with four for 42, while Craig Matthews picked
up three for 47.
New Zealand went for the runs and at tea appeared to have a good
chance of victory after a run-a-ball partnership of 64 between Ken
Rutherford and Stephen Fleming.
Fleming hit three 4s and a 6 in his 27, while Rutherford scored 56
from 60 balls, smashing the bowling attack to all parts of the ground.
A fine 101 from South African captain Hansie Cronje clinched the man
of the match award and enabled him to declare shortly before lunch at
308 for six.
South Africa 294 (D Cullinan 96) and 308 for 6 decl (H Cronje 101, G
Kirsten 76, A Hudson 64), New Zealand 328 (A Parore 89, B Young 74) and
181 (K Rutherford 56).
</TEXT>
