<DOCNO>GH950309-000044</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950309-000044</DOCID>
<DATE>950309</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Stream in full flow</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>TOM MCCONNELL</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>26</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484855</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ROYAL Stream, one of the most impressive performers of the season so
far, has earned himself a step up in class at Saturday's Cumberland
Farmers meeting at Dalston.
He has enjoyed effortless wins in confined races at Alnwick and Friars
Haugh, where he trotted up by 20 lengths.
He faces stiffer opposition in the John Peel Men's Open when one of
his rivals will be Mandika, dual winner of open races at Alnwick and
Lanark, and Gunmetal Boy, successful at the Buccleuch last year.
Kevin Anderson plans to run Jimmy River at the Tynedale meeting on
Sunday, believing that his mount will appreciate the extra half mile at
Corbridge.
Press for Action could go well in the Owners' Association race, but he
has unseated David Mactaggart twice this season. Buckle It Up, ridden by
David's younger brother, Jeremy, could be the better prospect.
There are 10 races on the Dalston card and nine at Corbridge next day.
</TEXT>
