<TEXT>
IN your report on Church of Scotland chaplaincies in universities and
elsewhere you state that universities currently meet only 50% of the
costs (March 1).
I do not know what happens in other universities but the University of
Glasgow receives no help from the church in this matter. The university
considers that the work of chaplaincy is vital and therefore finances it
