<HEADLINE>A real job</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>979484895</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
E KEATING implies that teaching is not a real job (March 3).
Such a statement is one of profound ignorance. It most certainly is a
real job dealing with youngsters in the classroom on a daily basis with
its attendant stresses and strains.
E Keating's further absurd notion that teachers should be banned from
driving on a permanent basis is one of the most bizarre remarks which I
have ever read.
John F Anderson,
55 Kingston Road,
Bishopton.
</TEXT>
