<DOCNO>GH950309-000107</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950309-000107</DOCID>
<DATE>950309</DATE>
<HEADLINE>No Headline Present</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>STEPHEN MCGREGOR</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484918</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Meanwhile, it emerged yesterday that the Tory cause in Perth and
Kinross could be further damaged by the possible emergence of a
candidate from the Referendum Party.
The party, backed by businessman Sir James Goldsmith, an MEP in
France, has a single-issue philosophy which broadly is that there should
be a referendum on whether Britain should agree to any further
integration in Europe.
A senior party source said yesterday that he thought it unlikely it
would field a candidate, although he did not totally rule out the
possibility.
If there was a plan to put up a candidate in Perth and Kinross, he
said,''nobody has told me.'' The spokesman said the party had had
contacts with the Tory Euro-sceptics at Westminster, and one of their
number said last night: ''I don't know about Perth and Kinross, but I
understood the Goldsmith lot were going to put up candidates in all
by-elections now.''
</TEXT>
