<HEADLINE>Mafia spree spreads fear</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484921</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CORLEONE: People frightened by a killing spree turned their backs on
an anti-Mafia march in the Sicilian town of Corleone yesterday,
birthplace of alleged ''Godfather'' Salvatore Riina. Journalists said
only a few hundred people, mainly students from the capital Palermo,
took part in the demonstration.
''The people of Corleone deserted the protest. In some cases they even
shut their windows as the march passed by,'' the news agency AGI
reported.
Hitmen have murdered nine people in Sicily in two weeks in what is
believed to be a warning that Riina's arrest had not broken the Mafia.
Back in January, hundreds of locals turned out to protest against the
first killing in Corleone for 16 years.
</TEXT>
