<HEADLINE>Gambia 'safer'</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484946</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BANJUL: Britain yesterday relaxed a travel warning issued after the
coup in Gambia last July. However the British High Commission in Banjul
said the outlook remained uncertain and that the security situation
could change without warning. Before the coup, Britons were half of the
130,000 tourists who visited Gambia each year.
