<HEADLINE>President picked</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484948</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ATHENS: The Greek Parliament elected veteran politician Costis
Stephanopoulos as the new state president on Wednesday, heading off
early national elections. Stephanopoulos, 68, who may be sworn in
tomorrow, succeeds President Constantine Karamanlis.
</TEXT>
