<DOCNO>GH950309-000140</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950309-000140</DOCID>
<DATE>950309</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Holy city party</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484951</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
JERUSALEM: The mayor yesterday announced plans for a lavish 3000th
birthday bash to celebrate Jerusalem as a Jewish capital. The
festivities will last 16 months from September and cost #6.8m. However
ultra-Orthodox Jewish leaders challenged the anniversary date as decades
premature, and Palestinians attacked it as a fresh attempt by Israel to
deny their claims to the city.
</TEXT>
