<HEADLINE>Statue offence</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979484956</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BEIRUT: A prosecutor yesterday demanded a life sentence with hard
labour against two Muslim guerrillas charged with blowing up a statue of
Jesus Christ in south Lebanon. The men, described as loyal to Palestine
Liberation Organisation chief Yasser Arafat, are accused of blowing up
the statue at a cemetery in Sidon last August in order to recreate the
atmosphere of Lebanon's 15-year civil war.
</TEXT>
